  "figure-34-8": (
    caption: [Appearance of thyroid gland follicles viewed through the microscope. When inactive, follicles are distended with colloid (stored T3 and T4) and epithelial cells are flattened. When active, the colloid disappears as hormones are secreted, and epithelial cells become enlarged.],
