    caption: [Regulation of blood calcium in birds and mammals. PTH stimulates osteoclasts to release calcium from bone, increases calcium reabsorption in kidneys, and stimulates formation of 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D3 (which aids intestinal absorption). Calcitonin stimulates osteoblasts to deposit calcium in bone and allows calcium excretion.],
    path: "../fig/fig-2025-12-03-16-25-08.png"
